00:10:56.095 --> 00:10:57.720
He's not doing anything
with the mixer.

00:10:57.720 --> 00:10:59.690
He's just using the
ability for the disc

00:10:59.690 --> 00:11:02.345
to turn independently
of the platter.

00:11:02.345 --> 00:11:04.170
Let me pull up the
baby, this is the one

00:11:04.170 --> 00:11:07.360
I was going to show before.

00:11:07.360 --> 00:11:09.874
There we go.

00:11:09.874 --> 00:11:12.040
DJ QBERT: So the first
scratch you're going to learn

00:11:12.040 --> 00:11:13.222
is the baby scratch.

00:11:13.222 --> 00:11:16.736
It's basically the
easiest scratch to do.

00:11:16.736 --> 00:11:19.196
You don't need a fader.

00:11:19.196 --> 00:11:21.164
You just move the
record back and forth.

00:11:21.164 --> 00:11:24.312
There was a deal in 1975,
and this is how it sounds.

00:11:30.117 --> 00:11:30.950
